The police in Edo State have arrested and paraded 357 suspects for kidnapping, armed robbery, cultism, murder, rape, burglary, attempted murder and other criminal activities. The suspected criminals were yesterday paraded by Police Commissioner, Phillip Ogbadu, during a news conference, with a large cache of arms and ammunition recovered from the suspects also displayed. Ogbadu noted that the news conference was to showcase successes recorded by the command from February 5 to date. He said: â€œThe command is faced with violent crimes of kidnapping, armed robbery, cultism, murder, rape and burglary, among others. As such, the command has continued to devise security strategies to prevent criminal activities and to ensure a secure, safe and stable environment for economic growth and social interaction.